Johannesburg, Jan.
7th
Leaving Mauritius we flew over Reunion, a small
island which flies the French flas, then over Madagascar which is the fourth largest
island in the world.
Continuing across to the African coast, we flew over Lourenco
Karoues in Portuguese Mozambique. It was there that the Gripsholm exchanged
merican refugees for Japanese. I remenber my old time secretary, Miss Forbes, who
worked for the State Dept. after we left China and was interned for several months
